22 hours ago, Ryan_Coates said:

will this be better than USI or closer too it i love usi mod and this mod

It really depends on what you're looking to get out of the mods. My opinion is that Pathfinder is easier to transport and setup ground bases. MKS is better at orbital stations, but can be used for ground bases. The WildBlue and USI mods have different resources and converters, but play ok together. The two mods don't share converters, but you can store CRP resources with Pathfinder in CRP play mode. Both mods have a different philosophies on resource management and distribution. I find that WildBlue resource management makes more sense than USI. Be aware that Pathfinder is heavily dependent on KIS. Any changes to KIS can present as bugs in Pathfinder until it's updated.

I'm not sure if I'm a total idiot or not  I downloaded the example craft file from the tutorial on building a base on the Pathfinder wiki. The parts that are meant to be in the storage blocks don't appear to me there to build the base and I'm struggling to add parts to the storage container. Not sure what I'm missing. Sorry just looking for some guidance. I'm just starting to learn about this mod and I thought I would follow the tutorial on building a basic base but that just doesn't seem to work currently. 

I'm running in KSP 1.7.2. My log file is here. I hope it works and you can view it.

You're not an idiot - the wiki is out of date and so is the craft. Not to say that the data on the wiki is completely useless, just that some things have changed since it was first written. An update is on Angel's to-do list, IIRC. 

Here, try the TBD 7 rover; it's a little more up to date (built v.1.4, IIRC. Maybe 1.5). I don't recall if I put a KIS resource transfer station and connector port in it or not; if not, you'll want to add them in the SPH before heading out. Use them to inflate the initial Pondy, and whatever you do, don't save your game with them still connected to one another; you'll cast "Summon Kraken" if you do. The TBD 7 is largely the same craft from the wiki, just with a few more bells and whistles. I've got a Mun outpost right now that started from one of these.

If you still have issues, say so and I'll see if I can't guide you through them.

Edited July 6, 2019 by capi3101

Thanks for that! I actually ended up getting pretty frustrated with it in the end. I managed to add parts to the container by res-assigning the storage away from storage and then assigning it back. Then the base plate blew up (KAS bug apparently it happens if you drop small parts??) and the snapping of the containers to the backplate just annoyed me too much. 

I will try again with this however, so thank you

Hey just replying to share the info I've gathered about continuing drill issues (on KSP 1.7.2).  I was having the issue with stock+buffalo drills not attaching in VAB and bugging it out; I saw you patched that so I updated to the latest, and this fixed the issue in VAB but I still couldn't launch those vehicles (it just returned me to space center).  After further investigation I was able to fix the stock drills by deleting the MM_Drills.cfg file in ModuleManagerPatches, then deleting the lines under "//Stock drill patches" at the bottom.  Of course I assume this removes capability to interact with gold strike nodes (which I honestly don't understand yet and haven't tried to find in any way so I'm not too concerned).  The buffalo drills that have the gold strike capability still bug out any vessel that I attempt to launch.  I'm currently trying to edit the buffalo drill cuz I love it's form factor and wanna use it.

I'm just sharing this info in case someone else has any trouble.  I'm using a number of mods such as Tac-LS, KIS, KAS, Tweakscale, Astronomers, Interstellar, DMagic, EL, Dangit, Near-Futures, SCANsat, RemoteTech, RealChute, Tarsier, PlanetaryBaseSomething, TextureReplacer, DistantObject, EVE, SuicidalInsanity's Stockalikes, Kerbal Atomics, number of other graphical mods, and some others I'm too lazy to list all.  

Edited July 6, 2019 by Natas_Enasni

The Saddle can be quite explosive - it's annoyed me on more than one occasion (the time it exploded on Gilly, and then took the Pondy with it - that time, I about rage quit; didn't because I was at on break my paying job at the time and I wanted to keep said paying job). There is a bit of advice on the wiki about not attaching it to the ground; it's 50/50 on how often that actually works.

First rule of Pathfinder - before you add anything, quicksave. If anything explodes, revert. Expect it to float afterwards...

Down here, you'll float too...

I guess my post got deleted when I edited it; well I'm not writing all that over again.  Just popping in to say that in KSP 1.7.2 with a lotta mods like Tac-LS, +a bunch I'm not listing again (thx forums) I was having continuing drill issues when using Pathfinder.  I saw that you patched it so I updated to the latest (Pathfinder 1.33.4), and this did fix the drill issue in the VAB.  However the vessels wouldn't launch and I would be returned to Space Center.  So I deleted MM_Drills.cfg in ModuleManagerPatches, and I deleted the lines under "stock drill patches" in the GoldStrikesomething.cfg in Resources.  This fixed the stock drills, but the buffalo drills and other WBI drills with stock gold strike functionality failed to launch vessels.  Those were easily remedied by marking out with // the bits in the part cfg related to pathfinder gold strike stuff.  Tbh I don't know what the gold strike functionality is yet, but if no one else has noticed this failing then it must be conflicting with some common mod.   Just sharing in case someone finds this info useful.

I managed to trace the issue I was having with the Pipelines (I had adjusted the values for fifteen tonnes to a 100-kilometer Eve orbit in both configuration files but was not seeing any effect) to the persistence file - turns out the maxKineticEnergy values weren't being updated after I'd changed the value in the configuration files (i.e. I could've changed the config files to my heart's content and it would've accomplished nothing). It was necessary for me to manually update the values in the persistence file to the desired values (Notepad++ made this task much less daunting; KML failed me for once). Of course, at the default value the maximum you can hope to send up to a 125-kilometer Eve orbit (3,147 m/s) is 0.597 tonnes, which is about what I was seeing.
